Prince Christopher of Yugoslavia, a relative of  Prince Philip, the husband of Queen Elizabeth II, has been killed in a road  accident in Scotland, it was announced overnight Sunday.
Christopher Caradjordgevic, 34, was the son of the late prince Andrei of  Yugoslavia and Christina Margarete van Eyck. He died Saturday.
The prince was known as Christopher George on the Scottish island of  Islay, in the Hebrides, where he had been teaching science at a highschool.
